org.eclipse.wst.jsdt.core
Interface IImportContainer

All Superinterfaces:
IJavaScriptElement, ILookupScope, IParent, ISourceReference
public interface IImportContainer
extends IJavaScriptElement, IParent, ISourceReference

Represents an import container is a child of a JavaScript unit that contains all (and only) the import declarations. If a JavaScript unit has no import declarations, no import container will be present.

This interface is not intended to be implemented by clients.

This Interface only applies to ECMAScript 4 which is not yet supported Provisional API: This class/interface is part of an interim API that is still under development and expected to change significantly before reaching stability. It is being made available at this early stage to solicit feedback from pioneering adopters on the understanding that any code that uses this API will almost certainly be broken (repeatedly) as the API evolves.

IImportDeclaration getImport(java.lang.String name)
